Here is a C++ program that counts the occurrences of a word in a text file:
```cpp
#include <fstream>
#include <string>

int main() {
    std::string word;
    std::cout << "Enter the word to search for: ";
    std::cin >> word;

    std::ifstream file("text.txt");
    int count = 0;
    std::string line;
    while (getline(file, line)) {
        size_t pos = line.find(word);
        while (pos != std::string::npos) {
            count++;
            pos = line.find(word, pos + 1);
        }
    }

    std::cout << "The word " << word << " appears " << count << " times." << std::endl;
} 
```

This program:

- Prompts the user to enter a word to search for
- Opens the text.txt file
- Initializes a count to 0 
- Reads the file line by line
- Checks if the word appears in the current line using std::string::find
- If found, increments the count and finds the next occurrence of the word in the line 
- Prints the total count of the word at the end

